ce:section.ce:para:
UV–vis diffuse reflectance spectroscopy (DRS) was used to study the optical properties and band gap energy values (Eg
                        ) of the as-prepared photocatalysts. And the UV–vis absorption spectra of the pure BiVO4, N-CQDs/BiVO4, Cu2O/BiVO4 and BiVO4/N-CQDs/Cu2O are illustrated in Fig. 6
                        a. For the pure BiVO4, the maximal absorbance wavelength is approximately 550 nm and this result is consistent with the previous reports [32,33]. After N-CQDs and Cu2O modified on the surface of BiVO4, the N-CQDs/BiVO4 and Cu2O/BiVO4 composites exhibited an enhanced optical absorption in visible region. Notably, BiVO4/N-CQDs/Cu2O composite possesses the strongest optical absorption in the range of 500–800 nm compared with other photocatalysts. The improvement of visible light harvesting ability could ascribed to Cu2O provided multiple reflection of visible light [34]. Furthermore, the N-CQDs could play as photosensitizer to further enhance the visible light absorption ability [29].
